<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The field is declared as a mutable void *: "void *crc_cls;". In the shown code it is used as an opaque closure passed to content-reader callbacks (e.g. response->crc_cls = response;) and is not intended to be modified through that pointer. Per MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13 the pointer should be const-qualified when possible (i.e. const void *crc_cls). Therefore this declaration is a violation unless the closure is actually modified via crc_cls elsewhere in the code (no such modification is shown).
</scenario>
